new sincerity” talk merges with transnational pleas to “revive sincerity.” This essential study stands squarely at the intersection of the history of emotions, media studies, and post-Soviet studies to shed light on a new cultural reality—one that is profoundly affecting creative thought, artistic expression, and lifestyle virtually everywhere.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCulture. 0aSincerity and literature. 0aSincerity. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Eastern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2017z9783110547764oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106389810 cprintz978030021398040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224832423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300224832/original  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-064982-6  Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017